ADDITIONAL_DESCRIPTION:
Standard options
  • ABS material — Strong, yet ultra-light for seemingly weightless protection
  • Low profile design — Offers a low center of gravity for better balance
  • Rear padded suspension — Provides additional level of comfort on the wearers’ neck
  • 4-position harness points — Allows you to move the harness forward, backward, up or down – allowing for the most optimal position for ultimate comfort
  • Replaceable sweat band — Padded fabric and polyurethane foam for all day wear
  • Vented pressure pad — Keeps the straps in place providing an additional level of comfort
  • Easy to grasp triangle knob — Adjusts the suspension from 6 1/2 to 8-inch hat sizes
  • Swinging hinge points — Allows you to find the most comfortable position on the back of your head
Vented options
  • Same options as standard Ridgeline with the addition of air vents at top and rear of hardhat, which help to circulate air and keep the head cool and dry

Kits contain the essentials for new hire and temporary workers. Includes white standard hard hat (ANSI Z89. 1), disposable corded ear plus (NRR 31), Class 2 Level 2 safety vest (sizes L – 2XL), foam nitrile palm coated gloves, and Intruder eye protection (clear or gray).

Sizes
  • Kit with clear lens safety glass and Large safety vest – NHCL
  • Kit with clear lens safety glass and X-Large safety vest – NHCXL
  • Kit with clear lens safety glass and 2X-Large safety vest – NHCX2
  • Kit with gray lens safety glass and Large safety vest – NHGL
  • Kit with gray lens safety glass and X-Large safety vest – NHGXL
  • Kit with gray lens safety glass and 2X-Large safety vest – NHGX2
Cap Style Hard Hat
  • Exceeds ANSI Z89. 1-2009, Type 1, Class C, G, and E for industrial head protection
  • Low profile design.
  • Shell constructed from High Density Polyethylene materials.
  • Rain trough on sides and back of helmet channel moisture away.
  • Snap Lock suspension features "tuck away" adjustments for all day, hassle free wear.
  • Soft brow pad, suspension and headbands are replaceable.
DP1001
  • NRR 31dB / SNR 36dB
  • Disposable Corded Earplugs.
  • Contoured fit disposable polyurethane ear plugs.
  • Plug gently expands and self adjusts to all size ear canals.
Safety Vest
  • ANSI/ISEA 107 - 2010 / Class 2 Level 2
  • Available in large, extra-large and 2X large.
  • Hi-Vis lightweight polyester mesh material.
  • 2 inch silver reflective material around bottom and over shoulders.
  • Zipper front closure.
  • Chest pocket with hook and loop closure.
  • Deep and wide inside pocket.
Intruder
  • Exceeds ANSI Z87. 1 high impact, CE EN166, CAN/CSA Z94. 3-07, AS/NZS 1337
  • Available in clear (S4110S) or gray (S4120S) lens.
  • Lightweight, frameless protection.
  • Superior comfort and fit.
  • Scratch resistant polycarbonate lens provides 99% UVA/B/C protection.

​

Foam Nitrile Palm Coated Gloves
  • Available in large - size 9
  • Foam nitrile (NBR) is the most versatile coating offering tremendous barrier against a wide range of workplace hazards.
  • It provides superior wear and solid resistance to snags, punctures, abrasion, and cuts.
  • Nitrile coating on 15-gauge seamless nylon lining that stretches to the hand for excellent dexterity and comfort.
  • Glove features easy on and off, superior dry grip, tactile sensitivity, and is machine washable.
  • The palm coating allows airflow through back of glove for cooler comfort.
  • Knitwrist cuff holds glove in place and keeps debris out.
